h3. Summary

Whenever using WAS JQL operator at the back with brackets, it will appear as error. When the WAS operator is moved to the front or an additional space at the back is inserted, the error disappears.

*Note:* Despite the error showing up, the JQL still can be executed with the expected outcome.

Example of an affected JQL:
{code:java}
project = TEST AND (assignee = user1 OR assignee was user2)
{code}
List of JQL examples with the outcomes:
 * project = TEST AND assignee was user1 \{Okay}
 * project = TEST AND (assignee was user1) \{Error}
 * project = TEST AND (assignee was user1) \{Okay}
(i) There is a space at the end of the JQL

 * project = TEST AND (assignee = user1 OR assignee was user2) \{Error}
 * project = TEST AND (assignee was user1 OR assignee = user2) \{Okay}

h3. Expected Results

JQL search bar shows no error
h3. Actual Results

JQL search bar shows error but is still able to execute it with the expected outcome
 !JQLSearchbar.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Workaround
 # Simply execute the JQL
 # Reorder the WAS operator to not be at the back
{code:java}
project = TEST AND (assignee was user2 OR assignee = user1)
{code}
 # Add an additional space at the back of the JQL
{code:java}
project = TEST AND (assignee was user1) 
{code}
(i) There is a space at the end of the JQL

{{\{code:sql\}}} in Jira recognizes {{-- comment}} but not {{/* comment */}}, which is supported by the Transact-SQL (T-SQL) language in Microsoft SQL Server. Please add syntax highlighting for that, too. It could be part of {{\{code:sql\}}} or have a distinct language identifier such as {{\{code:mssql\}}} or {{\{code:t-sql\}}}.

{code:sql}
SELECT
  number_of_protons /* comment */,
  relative_atomic_mass -- comment
FROM elements;
{code}

According to the Microsoft documentation for [Slash Star (Block Comment) (Transact-SQL)|https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/t-sql/language-elements/slash-star-comment-transact-sql?view=sql-server-2017], comments of this type can nest.

